# Functional Requirements

## Overview

This document defines the functional requirements for FlowDesk. Functional requirements describe the core functionality that the system must provide to meet user needs and business objectives.

---

# 1. User Authentication

### FR-001
The system shall allow users to register an account.

### FR-002
The system shall allow registered users to log in using their email address and password.

### FR-003
The system shall allow users to securely log out of the system.

### FR-004
The system shall allow users to reset forgotten passwords.

### FR-005
The system shall validate user credentials before granting access.

---

# 2. Business Management

### FR-006
The system shall allow business owners to create a business profile.

### FR-007
The system shall allow business owners to edit their business information.

### FR-008
The system shall allow business owners to upload a business logo.

### FR-009
The system shall allow business owners to configure business operating hours.

### FR-010
The system shall allow business owners to manage multiple business locations in future releases.

---

# 3. Dashboard

### FR-011
The system shall display a personalised dashboard after successful login.

### FR-012
The dashboard shall display today's appointments.

### FR-013
The dashboard shall display business statistics.

### FR-014
The dashboard shall display recent business activity.

---

# 4. Staff Management

### FR-015
The system shall allow business owners to add employees.

### FR-016
The system shall allow business owners to edit employee details.

### FR-017
The system shall allow business owners to deactivate employee accounts.

### FR-018
The system shall assign role-based permissions to employees.

---

# 5. Customer Management

### FR-019
The system shall allow business owners and authorised employees to add customers.

### FR-020
The system shall allow authorised users to edit customer information.

### FR-021
The system shall allow users to search for customers.

### FR-022
The system shall display customer profiles and booking history.

---

# 6. Service Management

### FR-023
The system shall allow business owners to create services.

### FR-024
The system shall allow business owners to edit service details.

### FR-025
The system shall allow business owners to remove services.

### FR-026
The system shall store service pricing and duration.

---

# 7. Booking Management

### FR-027
The system shall allow customers to create appointments online.

### FR-028
The system shall prevent double bookings.

### FR-029
The system shall display available booking slots.

### FR-030
The system shall allow business owners to approve or reject bookings.

### FR-031
The system shall allow appointments to be rescheduled.

### FR-032
The system shall allow appointments to be cancelled.

### FR-033
The system shall update the calendar automatically after booking changes.

---

# 8. Calendar

### FR-034
The system shall provide daily, weekly, and monthly calendar views.

### FR-035
The system shall display appointment details within the calendar.

### FR-036
The system shall allow users to access appointment information directly from the calendar.

---

# 9. Reports & Analytics

### FR-037
The system shall generate booking reports.

### FR-038
The system shall generate customer reports.

### FR-039
The system shall generate revenue reports.

### FR-040
The system shall display business performance statistics.

---

# 10. Notifications

### FR-041
The system shall send booking confirmation emails.

### FR-042
The system shall send appointment reminder notifications.

### FR-043
The system shall notify users when appointments are cancelled or rescheduled.

---

# 11. User Profile

### FR-044
The system shall allow users to view their profile.

### FR-045
The system shall allow users to update their personal information.

### FR-046
The system shall allow users to change their password.

---

# 12. Platform Administration

### FR-047
The system shall allow platform administrators to manage registered businesses.

### FR-048
The system shall allow platform administrators to suspend business accounts.

### FR-049
The system shall allow platform administrators to monitor platform usage.

### FR-050
The system shall allow platform administrators to manage support requests.

---

